DAY05:lists
1.What Are HTML Lists?
   HTML lists are used to organize and display a group of related items in a structured way on a webpage. 
    Lists improve readability and structure.

2.types of list in HTML
   1.Unorderd List (<ul>)
     *Used when the order of items doesn't matter.
     *Displayed with bullets by default.
     *Each item inside the list is written using <li> tag.

    3.ordered list(<ol>)
      *Used when the order does matter.
      *Items are automatically numbered by default.
      *Also uses <li> for each list in item.

     3. Description List (<dl>)
       * Used for terms and their descriptions.
        *Includes three tags:
             <dl>: list container
             <dt>: defines the term
              <dd>: defines the description   

 3.When to Use Each List
        List Type                   	Use When…
            <ul>             	Order doesn’t matter (bullet list)
            <ol>            	Order matters (steps, ranking)
            <dl>	            You want term–definition pairs
